label.value: Positive CSF human T-lymphotropic virus type I antibody positivity

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of human T-lymphotropic virus type I.

label.value: Positive chlamydia trachomatis urine nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Chlamydia trachomatis nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

value.value: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against streptococcal deoxyribonuclease-B (ADN-B). Almost all group A streptococci have this antigen and a strong elevation of the antibody is observed in patients with acute rheumatic fever, acute glomerulonephritis and other streptococcal infections.

label.value: Positive streptococcus A rapid antigen detection test

value.value: Positive detection of a group A streptococcal antigen in a test perforned on a throat swab.

definition.value: Growth of a mycobacteria in a culture derived from synovial fluid.

label.value: Positive mycobacterial synovial nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of mycobacteria in the synovial fluid by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label.value: Positive bloodstream babesia nucleic acid pathogen test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of genus Babesia (parasite) in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).
Detection of nucleic acid of an influenza virus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label.value: Positive bloodstream parainfluenza virus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of parainfluenza virus in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label.value: Positive bloodstream adenovirus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of an adenovirus in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).
The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Francisella tularensis.

label.value: Positive bloodstream MERS coronavirus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label.value: Positive nasopharyngeal corynebacterium diphtheriae nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of Corynebacterium diphtheriae in nasopharyngeal secretions by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

value.value: Visualization of at least one louse on visual inspection of the head hair. Use of a bright light, magnifying lens, or fine-toothed comb (lice comb) can aid in diagnosis.
The presence in the skin of the glabellar region of an increased degree of wrinkling (irregular folds and indentations) of the skin as compared with age-related norms.

Hyperpigmented macules with a reticulate (net-like) pattern involving the neck, axillae, groins, and other flexures like the inframammary folds in females. Histopathology shows orthokeratosis or hyperkeratosis, thinning of the suprapapillary epithelium, elongation of the rete ridges, hyperpigmentation of the basal layer, and follicular cysts. A perivascular lymphohistiocytic infiltrate can be observed in the papillary dermis.

Abnormally increased proportion of filtered urate that is excreted in the urine as calculated using the concentrations of urate and creatinine in both blood and urine. Clinically this manifests as uric acid wasting.

definition.value: The amount of creatine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.
The amount of creatine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Elevated circulating type I procollagen aminoterminal propeptide concentration

value.value: The concentration of type I procollagen aminoterminal propeptide in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. The aminoterminal propeptide of type I procollagen (PINP) in serum is a sensitive indicator of the synthesis of type I collagen.
Concentration or activity of S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase (EC 3.3.1.1) below the lower limit of normal. FECH enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including erythrocytes and liver.

definition.value: The concentration of dopamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Concentration of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide (AICA-riboside) in red blood cells is above the upper limit of normal.
Concentration of monomethylsterols (such as 4alpha-monomethylsterol) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of dimethylsterols in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label.value: Elevated circulating C-terminal fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration

value.value: The concentration of the C-terminal portion of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is outside of the limits of normal.

definition.value: FGF23 is also known as phosphate-regulating hormone.

value.value: The amount of 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid (5-HIAA) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of thiosulfate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Thiosulfate is an oxyanion of sulfur with the chemical formula S2O3(2-).

label.value: Elevated circulating interleukin 1 receptor antagonist concentration

definition.value: The concentration of interleukin 1 receptor antagonist (IL-1RA) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label.value: Positive CSF West Nile virus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of West Nile virus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label.value: Positive CSF herpes simplex virus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of herpes simplex virus (HSV) nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.
A test result demonstrating the presence of a cryptococal antigen in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).
Growth of rubella virus in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label.value: Positive CSF treponema pallidum nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Treponema pallidum (syphillis) nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.
Concentration of tetrahydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.
The concentration of N-acetyl-aspartyl-glutamate (NAAG) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

N-acetyl-aspartyl-glutamate (NAAG) is the most abundant dipeptide in the brain, where it acts as a neuromodulator of glutamatergic synapses by activating presynaptic metabotropic glutamate receptor 3 (mGluR3).

label.value: Positive CSF Tropheryma whipplei bacteria microscopy

value.value: Demonstration of Tropheryma whipplei bacteria in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) my microscopic analysis.

definition.value: T. whipplei is a rod-shaped, Gram-positive bacterium.
The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of treponema pallidum (syphilis).

value.value: A stimulus triggered repetition of an action (echopraxia) or sound (echolalia) performed without the explicit awareness of an individual.

definition.value: Increased autofluorescence in areas adjacent to the central macula (but not including the very center).

A condition in which the limbs of a fetus are immobile or held in a rigid position. The limbs are consistently immobile and rigid. Fixed extremities can be observed during prenatal imaging (e.g., ultrasound).

The density of the deep peripapillary microvascular network (i.e., the number of blood vessels) is below the lower limit of normal. This finding is observable by optical coherence tomography angiography.
Inflammation of the skin and soft tissues of the outer ear.
In contrast to auricular chondritis, auriculitis does not specifically affect the cartilage of the ear.

label.value: Recent history of moisture in external ear canal

value.value: A recent history of being exposed to moisture in the external ear canal.

definition.value: Swimmer's ear may occur when excess moisture in the ear canal allows bacteria or fungi to grow more easily. Risk factors include swimming and use of ear buds while exercising (and sweating).

label.value: History of recent trauma to external ear canal

definition.value: Medical history of trauma to the external ear canal, including cotton-swab use, in recent weeks.

value.value: The amount of 4-tyramine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: This feature has been observed in Acrocapitofemoral dysplasia; See Figure 4 of PMID:12624140.

value.value: The concentration of 3-hydroxykynurenine in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Exaggerated posterior vertebral notches.

The distal epiphysis (rounded portion of bone at the far end of the tibia distal to the growth plate) has an abnormal cone-shaped appearance, that is, the epiphysis has a globular form at the bottom, tapering to a point at the top.

Low bone mass localized in the neck of the femur. Osteoporosis is defined based on a T-score of -2.5 or lower (bone mineral density of 2.5 or more standard deviations below that of a normal young adult).
